{{Quote|I've been watching ''WandaVision'' for the last week, and the love [[Wanda Maximoff|you two]] have is real.|Darcy Lewis to [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]]|Breaking the Fourth Wall}}
Doctor '''Darcy Lewis''' is a former student of political science at [[Culver University]] who became an intern for [[Erik Selvig]], and an assistant to [[Jane Foster]]. While working in [[New Mexico]], Lewis came into contact with [[Asgardians]] when [[Thor]] arrived on [[Earth]], only to be followed by the [[Warriors Three]], [[Sif]] and the [[Destroyer]]. Lewis and Foster became focused on understanding the [[Bifrost Bridge]] and when Thor returned to Earth in [[2013]], Lewis assisted him in his war against [[Malekith]] and the [[Dark Elves]]. Returning to school, Lewis graduated with a doctorate in astrophysics.

In [[2023]], three weeks after the [[Blip]], Lewis was recruited by [[S.W.O.R.D.]] to investigate a [[Westview Anomaly|mysterious supernatural phenomenon]] occurring in the town of [[Westview]], [[New Jersey]]. Lewis herself discovered that the town was actually trapped in an simulation reminiscent of past sitcoms, and that [[Wanda Maximoff]] was the culprit. During her mission, Lewis befriended [[Jimmy Woo]], [[Monica Rambeau]] and [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] in her quest to dispel the Hex and was instrumental in the arrest of S.W.O.R.D. Director [[Tyler Hayward]], who had violated the [[Sokovia Accords]].

[[2025|Two years later]], Lewis supported Foster when she was undergoing chemotherapy for Stage IV cancer and urged her friend to continue the treatments rather than ignoring them to focus on scientific pursuits.

==Biography==
===Discovery in New Mexico===
====Working with Scientists====
{{Quote|She was the only applicant.|[[Jane Foster]]|Thor (film)}}
Darcy Lewis became a political science student at [[Culver University]]. She went to work with [[Jane Foster]] and [[Erik Selvig]] as an intern for six college credits.{{Ref|MSCE}} In [[2010|June 2010]], he group traveled to [[New Mexico]], where a series of spatial anomalies that Foster believed to be precursors to a [[wormhole]] were taking place.{{Ref|T}}

====Meeting Thor====
{{Quote|You know, for a homeless guy, [[Thor|he]] is pretty cut.|Darcy Lewis|Thor (film)}}
[[File:2011 thor 040.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis in her van with [[Jane Foster]]]]
Lewis was traveling in a van with [[Jane Foster]] and [[Erik Selvig]], when the mysterious weather event subject of Foster's research unexpectedly turned into a powerful vortex before them. As they struggled with the zero-visibility conditions, the van collided with a man who had stumbled out of the dust into their path. The man, who only announced himself as [[Thor]], began raving on about a [[Mjølnir|hammer]] and the [[Bifrost Bridge|Bifrost]], prompting Lewis to taser the supposedly delusional stranger. With the man knocked out, the group took him to the hospital.{{Ref|T}}

====Learning about Thor====
[[File:MAN-18363R-560x373.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis works with [[Jane Foster]] and [[Erik Selvig]]]]
The following day, Lewis made a surprise discovery when she noticed the figure of a [[Thor|man]] in one of the photographic images captured from the atmospheric event. While [[Jane Foster]] realized that the newcomer might be able to shed some light on the event, [[Erik Selvig]] was more skeptical, sparking a lengthy disagreement that Lewis only rarely weighed in on to support the more fanciful elements of Foster's theories.

Lewis continued to tag along with the scientists, providing numerous observations about their rapidly changing situation that were helpful to them.{{Ref|T}}

====S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Arrival====
[[File:Jane left with nothing.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis witnesses [[Jane Foster]]'s work taken]]
When they returned to the [[Smith Motors|base]], they discovered [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agents confiscating their equipment and research. Lewis watched as [[Erik Selvig]] tried to calm an angry [[Jane Foster]] down, due to knowing how serious the actual situation was. [[Phil Coulson]] told Foster they needed to take all of her possessions, and attempted to compensate her. Despite her pleas, all of Foster's belongings, including her research that was on the verge of an extraordinary discovery, were taken.
S.H.I.E.L.D. then left the base, so they then sat on the roof of the building, commiserating the loss of their property, as Selvig informed them of who the people that they encountered were.{{Ref|T}}

====[[Battle of Puente Antiguo]]====
[[File:Jane sees Sif and W3.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis sees [[Sif]] and the [[Warriors Three]] arrive]]
Later, four [[Asgardians]] appeared at the base, much to Lewis, [[Jane Foster]], and [[Erik Selvig]]'s shock and awe. They entered the base and introduced themselves as [[Sif]] and the [[Warriors Three]], and Lewis watched as [[Thor]] conversed with them.
[[File:Jane and Erik.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis watches [[Thor]] confront the [[Destroyer]]]]
When another vortex formed out in the desert, they all went outside to look at it, where Thor realized that the [[Destroyer]] had been sent down, causing him to warn Foster, Lewis, and Selvig to leave. However, they stayed to help and Lewis watched as Sif and the Warriors Three battled the Destroyer. When the Destroyer quickly overpowered them, Thor ordered to them run away before they were caught in the destruction. When Thor seemingly died, Lewis watched as Foster ran out to him, but she was pulled back by Selvig. They watched as [[Mjølnir]] was returned to Thor, which helped revive him, and allow him to defeat the Destroyer.
[[File:Jane is left behind.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis watches [[Thor]] leave]]
Lewis stayed at the site with Foster and Selvig and watched as Thor and the other Asgardians departed [[Earth]]. They watched as the [[Bifrost Bridge]] opened to begin producing dark lighting clouds, much to their concern. After some time, they then saw the Bifrost opening completely disappear before them, and decided to leave.{{Ref|T}}

===Search for Thor===
====Assisting Jane Foster====
Lewis tried to help [[Jane Foster]] find a way to bring [[Thor]] back to [[Earth]]. They built a device to open a [[wormhole]], but it failed. Lewis told Foster to wait since Thor promised to return. However, one year passed and Lewis began to doubt that Thor would return at all. When Thor's brother [[Loki]] came to Earth, [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] contacted Foster and sent her to [[Tromsø]], [[Norway]] to an Astrophysics Lab.{{Ref|TTDWP1}} Once arrived in Norway, nobody in the lab had any idea why she and Foster were sent there. Lewis hacked into the computer and found live footage of Thor in [[New York City]], and she showed the video to Foster. Discovering from [[Erik Selvig]] that Thor had left Earth, Lewis comforted her friend, telling her that Thor would return again, but Foster disagreed and gave up.{{Ref|TTDWP2}}

====[[Convergence]]====
[[File:Phase Meter1.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis and [[Ian Boothby]] arriving at the site]]
{{Quote|I am not getting stabbed in the name of science. It's okay, we're Americans!"<br>"Is that supposed to make them like us?|Darcy Lewis and [[Jane Foster]]|Thor: The Dark World}}
In [[2013|November 2013]], Lewis and [[Jane Foster]] were called to [[London]] by [[Erik Selvig]], who had been there for several weeks researching a new series of anomalies. When they got there, they found Selvig missing and took up residence in his flat. During this time, Lewis hired [[Ian Boothby]] as her own intern. After several days without any word from Selvig, Lewis discovered that Selvig's [[Phase Meter|scientific equipment]] was acting up, and brought this information to Foster, interrupting her date with a man named [[Richard Madison]]. The pair, accompanied by Boothby, followed the signals to an abandoned warehouse where the laws of physics were going haywire and various portals had opened up. While Lewis and Boothby were distracted by the events, Foster disappeared.{{Ref|TTDW}}

====Return of Thor====
[[File:Urlcc.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis witness [[Thor]] taking away [[Jane Foster]]]]
{{Quote|Look at you, still all muscly and everything. How's space?"<br>"Space is fine.|Darcy Lewis and [[Thor]]|Thor: The Dark World}}
Having not being able to locate [[Jane Foster]] for five hours, Lewis called the {{WPS|Metropolitan Police Service|Metropolitan Police}}, only for Foster to appear as suddenly as she vanished. When the police were about to arrest the group for trespassing on private property, [[Thor]] suddenly appeared, having been alerted by [[Heimdall]] to Foster's disappearance. While Foster was speaking with Thor, Lewis confirmed that they were likely going to be arrested, as she warned Foster about this, before commenting that Thor was still muscly, and questioning how [[Asgard]] was, to which Thor confirmed that it was fine. When one of the officers tried to forcefully arrest Foster, her body reacted by unleashing a mysterious [[Aether|energy]] that forced everyone away from her. Before the police could react, Thor left with Foster via [[Bifrost Bridge]], leaving a stupefied Lewis behind.{{Ref|TTDW}}

====Search for Erik Selvig====
[[File:SelvigandDarcy-TTDW.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis with [[Ian Boothby]] and [[Erik Selvig]]]]
In Foster's absence, Lewis was left with Boothby to try to locate Selvig and to make sense of the situation. After failing to page [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] for assistance, Lewis saw a newscast of Selvig running around naked at [[Stonehenge]], and together they traced him to a local mental institution. After bailing Selvig out and nearly being pummeled by birds affected by [[Wormhole|dimensional portals]], Lewis, Boothby, and Selvig returned to Foster's [[Jane Foster's Apartment|apartment]] and studied Selvig's research over the strange anomalies, which were revealed to be echoes of the [[Convergence]].{{Ref|TTDW}}

====Return of Thor====
[[File:JaneDarcy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis listening to the [[Convergence]] discussion]]
[[Jane Foster]] and [[Thor]] eventually returned, having traveled to [[Asgard]], then to [[Svartalfheim]], where they discovered a portal that returned them safely to [[Earth]]. Foster revealed that [[Malekith]] sought to use the [[Aether]] to obliterate the [[Nine Realms]] through the [[Convergence]].{{Ref|TTDW}}

====[[Battle of Greenwich]]====
[[File:Darcy and Ian.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis and [[Ian Boothby]] see the [[Dark Elves]]]]
{{Quote|You saved my life.|Darcy Lewis to [[Ian Boothby]]|Thor: The Dark World}}
Together, the group confronted [[Malekith]] at Greenwich, where, while [[Thor]] fought him, Lewis and her friends dealt with his minions via teleportation devices created by [[Erik Selvig]]. Lewis and [[Ian Boothby]] were separated from the others and were nearly killed by a platoon of Dark Elf soldiers. Fortunately, a [[Frost Beasts|Frost Beast]] was teleported to their exact location and killed the [[Dark Elves]], inadvertently saving the pair. However, they were teleported away accidentally by Foster, mostly to her indifference, where the bemused pair were attacked by two Dark Elves. Lewis fell on the ground but Boothby saved Lewis from their assailants by picking up a floating car and slamming it onto the elves, fatally crushing them. After acknowledging he had saved her life, Lewis passionately embraced him in a kiss, which Foster and Selvig witnessed when they used the teleporter. Lewis awkwardly dropped Boothby just as [[Mjølnir]] sailed past them intent on reaching its owner. Lewis and Boothby arrived to see Foster and Thor nearly been crushed by the dark elves ship. Fortunately, Selvig used the device to teleport it elsewhere where it crushed Malekith to death. Relieved her friends were alright, an overjoyed Lewis kissed Boothby more passionately.{{Ref|TTDW}}

====Aftermath of the Battle====
[[File:Lewis Ian.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis witnesses [[Thor]]'s return]]
Afterwards, Lewis returned to Foster's apartment with Boothby, Foster, and Selvig. A few days later, Lewis witnessed Thor returning in the [[Bifrost Bridge]] to stay on Earth with Foster.{{Ref|TTDW}}

===Getting Her Doctorate===
Sometime later, Lewis completed her university studies and gained a doctorate.{{Ref|WV104}} In [[2018]], she survived the [[Snap]]; however, she lost both [[Jane Foster]] and [[Erik Selvig]] to it.<ref name="DarcySnap">[https://comicbook.com/tv-shows/news/wandavision-darcy-lewis-jimmy-woo-avengers-endgame-thanos-snap/ WandaVision Stars on Whether Darcy Lewis and Jimmy Woo Survived Thanos' Snap]</ref>

===[[Westview Anomaly]]===
====Arrival at the S.W.O.R.D. Base====
[[File:Darcy Lewis (WandaVision).png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis arrives at the [[S.W.O.R.D. Response Base|S.W.O.R.D. Base]]]]
{{Quote|Astrophysics. We got the full clown car. It means whatever the [[Scarlet Witch|threat]] is, [[S.W.O.R.D.]] clearly has no idea what they're dealing with.|Darcy Lewis|We Interrupt This Program}}
In [[2023|November 2023]], a few weeks after the [[Blip]], Lewis was called by [[S.W.O.R.D.]] to help them find out what was happening in [[Westview]], [[New Jersey]]. Lewis rode in a van with several other scientists and inquired about what they all specialized in. Upon arriving at the [[S.W.O.R.D. Response Base]], Lewis was greeted by a S.W.O.R.D agent who took her to her workstation.{{Ref|WV104}}

====Discovering the Show====
[[File:Jimmy Woo & Darcy Lewis.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis discovers the ''WandaVision'' show]]
{{Quote|Entwined was a broadcast frequency. So I had [[Tyler Hayward|your]] goons pick me up a sweet vintage TV. And when I plug this bad boy in, ''voilà'', sound and picture."<br>"So you're saying the universe created a sitcom starring two [[Avengers]]?|Darcy Lewis and [[Jimmy Woo]]|We Interrupt This Program}}
Upon monitoring the levels of radiation coming from [[Westview]], Lewis picked up high levels of {{WPS|Cosmic Microwave Background|CMBR}} and saw that there were longer waves imposed amongst it. Afterwards, she pulled out a device and tuned it which revealed the ''[[WandaVision]]'' show. [[Jimmy Woo]], [[Tyler Hayward]], and a few of his agents came over and saw the show also.{{Ref|WV104}}

====Finding Monica Rambeau====
[[File:Darcy Lewis (2023).png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis works with [[Jimmy Woo]]]]
{{Quote|One second, [[Monica Rambeau|Monica]] is standing there, and the next she isn't. Someone is censoring the broadcast."<br>"But where's Rambeau?|Darcy Lewis and [[Jimmy Woo]]|We Interrupt This Program}}
Once Lewis had discovered the broadcast, she and [[Jimmy Woo]] worked together in attempt to identify all the victims of the [[Westview Anomaly]]. One by one they identified most victims in order of appearance on the show. During it Lewis spotted [[Monica Rambeau]] and she asked Woo if he thought Rambeau was okay. They discussed what was going on and Lewis wished to experiment to see if they could reach inside Westview.
[[File:Screen-shot-2021-02-05-at-1-49-25-pm-1612550984.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis at the [[S.W.O.R.D. Response Base|S.W.O.R.D Base]]]]
Lewis planned when [[Wanda Maximoff]] was washing the dishes Woo would try and contact Maximoff by radio. During the test it looked as though it was working only for the broadcast to buffer. Lewis told Woo that the attempt failed and that he needed to head back to her. Woo and Lewis watched the broadcast in which Rambeau had a larger role. When Rambeau mentioned [[Ultron]] killing [[Quicksilver]], Lewis asked Woo if their reality had ever been mentioned. The broadcast buffered again, and the alarms went off. Lewis and Woo rushed out of the base to find out what had happened when they saw Rambeau being thrown out of Westview.{{Ref|WV104}}

====Working with Rambeau and Woo====
[[File:Darcy & Jimmy WV Episode 5.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis meets [[Monica Rambeau]]]]
Sometime later, Lewis alongside [[Jimmy Woo]] visited [[Monica Rambeau]], catching her up on what she had missed. Lewis gave Rambeau some clothes to wear and told her about an upcoming briefing with [[Tyler Hayward]]. In said briefing, Lewis watched as Hayward displayed a video of [[Wanda Maximoff]] stealing [[Vision]]'s corpse from the [[S.W.O.R.D. Headquarters]], as Lewis commented on how it was all very confusing.
[[File:Darcy, Monica & Woo.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis working with [[Jimmy Woo]] and [[Monica Rambeau]]]]
Later, Rambeau said that she wanted to go back into Westview, but Lewis pointed out the [[Hex]] could wipe her mind again. Rambeau explained to Lewis that everything in the Hex was real, to which Lewis replied stating that Maximoff must have a lot of power. They then discussed the [[Battle of Earth]], and how Maximoff could have killed [[Thanos/Cosmic Time Heist|Thanos]]. Woo said he could argue that [[Captain Marvel]] came close as well, prompting Lewis to note that her powers came from the [[Space Stone]]; however, Rambeau wanted to change the subject back to Maximoff. During the discussion, Rambeau had an idea and they went to where Rambeau's clothing was being stored. Rambeau shot at the clothing in which they discovered the clothing was her Bulletproof Vest. The discovery led them to the conclusion that everything in Westview was rewritten, which led Rambeau into the idea that if they sent something from the time period in it would not need to be changed.
[[File:Darcy & Woo watch Wanda.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis sees [[Wanda Maximoff]]'s confrontation]]
Sometime later, Lewis and Woo rushed out of the base after the alarms had gone off. [[Wanda Maximoff]] had left Westview to confront [[S.W.O.R.D.]] and Lewis watched her interaction with them.{{Ref|WV105}}

====Ejected from the Base====
[[File:Screenshot (23).png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis reacting to the sudden fight]]
{{Quote|Hey, there he is. The guy who almost got murdered by his own murder squad."<br>"You work for me?"<br>"I actually don't know.|Darcy Lewis and [[Tyler Hayward]]|All-New Halloween Spooktacular!}}
Following [[Wanda Maximoff]]'s confrontation with [[S.W.O.R.D.]], Lewis was angry with [[Tyler Hayward]], and how he had acted, as Lewis remarked about how he was nearly murdered by his own men. As Hayward questioned if Lewis worked for him, Lewis confessed that she was not actually sure about the chain of current command. Once their conversation had ended, Lewis, alongside [[Jimmy Woo]] and [[Monica Rambeau]], were ordered to leave the [[S.W.O.R.D. Response Base|Response Base]]. While they were being transported out of the base, Woo and Rambeau fought back and disarmed the S.W.O.R.D. agents, as Lewis remarked on how no one had told her the plan. She and the other two then changed into S.W.O.R.D uniforms and headed back inside of the base.{{Ref|WV106}}

====Discovering Project Cataract====
[[File:Monica, Woo & Darcy.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis discovers Project Cataract]]
{{Quote|I haven't made it through [[Tyler Hayward|Hayward]]'s last firewall. There's something big here, something that can help us, I know it.|Darcy Lewis to [[Monica Rambeau]]|All-New Halloween Spooktacular!}}
Not long after they broke back into the base, Lewis hacked into the [[S.W.O.R.D.]] database and looked through [[Tyler Hayward]]'s files. In this, Lewis found a section on [[Monica Rambeau]] and discovered that Rambeau's cells had been rewritten. Lewis looked through the files and found a project code named 'Cataract'. She saw that Hayward had a full map of [[Westview]] and a headcount of its residence, before Lewis noticed that [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] was being tracked by Hayward. Once Rambeau and [[Jimmy Woo]] agreed that they needed to leave, Lewis stayed behind to break through the final fire wall.{{Ref|WV106}}

====Hex Expansion====
[[File:Darcy absorbed into the Hex.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis is absorbed into the Hex]]
{{Quote|You know, part of me secretly wanted a guest spot on the show, but seriously, that sucked.|Darcy Lewis to [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]]|Breaking the Fourth Wall}}
Shortly, Lewis heard alarms go off and she headed out to find out what had happened. She saw [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] pleading for help after escaping the Hex. Lewis screamed at the S.W.O.R.D. agents to help him but was promptly reprimanded by [[Monti]] and handcuffed to a [[Humvee]], under the orders of [[Tyler Hayward]]. Lewis watched as Vision was torn apart bit by bit. When the Hex was expanded, Lewis was abandoned by the agents and became consumed into the Hex.{{Ref|WV106}}
[[File:Darcy Lewis Escape Artist.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis as the escape artist ]]
The next day, Lewis awakened in the Hex under the influence of [[Wanda Maximoff]]. She was shackled to a circus truck as the escape artist for the circus. [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] headed over to Lewis and asked her about the night before, in which Lewis remarked she had no clue who he was. Lewis released herself and walked away from Vision, who proceeded to follow, trying to remind of her investigation of the Maximoff Anomaly but she only responded she won't go out with him, until finally agreeing. An exasperated Vision distracted her and released her from the mind control.
[[File:Darcy & Vision.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis' self is freed by [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]]]]
As she regained her bearings, Lewis remarked that part of her secretly wanted a guest spot on the show only to feel disappointed by the role she was given. [[Monti]] rushed over to Lewis and commanded her alongside Vision to get on stage, but when she refused, he grabbed her arm. In return, Lewis punched him in the face. As they climbed into a food van, Lewis responded to Vision's inquiries, admitting she didn't know the status of his children nor the identity of the impostor "Pietro".
[[File:Darcy Vision.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis drives a food van with [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]]]]
As they drove back to Westview, Lewis filled Vision in on the events of the past few years. She told him of the [[Infinity War]] and how Maximoff had to kill him, but that sacrifice was rendered meaningless when [[Thanos]] used the [[Time Stone]] to reverse time and killed him again. They soon pulled to stop at a red light but as they tried to proceed, with Lewis noting it never rained in Westview, suddenly a work crew pulled up, blocking their way.

While waiting for the crew to finish, Vision asked what he was now if not [[J.A.R.V.I.S.]] or [[Ultron]]'s creation. Lewis could only speculate that Maximoff simply flipped a switch and brought him back to life, but she was clueless as to why Vision was unable to leave the Hex. Nonetheless, she assured him that the love between him and Maximoff was very real from watching ''WandaVision'' for the past week. Lewis' relief as the crew cleared out quickly evaporated as a crossing of school children continued to block the road; she rhetorically asked if puppies were the next impediment. Vision then left by phasing out of the truck and flying off to go meet Maximoff. Lewis said she would meet him there and continued to drive.{{Ref|WV107}}

====[[Battle of Westview]]====
[[File:Darcy Lewis (The Series Finale).png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis stops [[Tyler Hayward]]]]
{{Quote|Have fun in prison!|Darcy Lewis to [[Tyler Hayward]]|The Series Finale}}
By the time Lewis arrived into Westview's town square, she rammed the food van into [[Tyler Hayward]]'s Humvee, disabling it. After the [[Hex]] was gone, Lewis left before she could be questioned by the [[FBI]] and [[Eastview]] police, telling [[Monica Rambeau]] that "Debriefs are for the weak".{{Ref|WV109}}

===Time with Jane Foster===
[[File:Darcy with Jane.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lewis spends time with [[Jane Foster]] during her chemotherapy treatment]]
{{Quote|Jane, it's stage four.”<br>“Out of like, how many stages?”<br>“Four.|Darcy Lewis and [[Jane Foster]]|Thor: Love and Thunder}}
By [[2024]], Lewis was informed by [[Jane Foster]] that she had been diagnosed with cancer that had advanced to stage IV. Lewis accompanied Foster as much as possible to her chemotherapy appointments at the [[Puente Antiguo County Hospital]]. In [[2025]], Lewis told Foster not to try and fight the cancer alone because she had people who could help her. She then suggested she go to [[New Asgard]] to seek [[Thor]]’s help regarding it.{{Ref|TLaT}}

==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Thor: Love and Thunder. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|I thought you were a science major."<br>"Political science.|[[Erik Selvig]] and Darcy Lewis|Thor (film)}}
*'''Master Scientist''': [[File:WandaVision Darcy.jpg|thumb|250px|Lewis finds [[Wanda Maximoff]] in the [[Hex]]]] Through her work with [[Erik Selvig]] and [[Jane Foster]], Lewis acquired some degree of scientific knowledge; Lewis' background is better suited in political science. However, Lewis is skilled in accessing computerized information and noticing inconsistencies that even Selvig and Foster did not see. Sometime after the [[Battle of Greenwich]], Lewis returned to school and gained a doctorate in astrophysics, and was skilled enough in her field that she was enlisted by [[S.W.O.R.D.]] to aid in their investigation of [[Westview]]. She was able to find out that the [[Hex]] was emitting CMBR. This meant that if they hooked up an old TV, they could get a read on what is going on with [[Wanda Maximoff]]. She also had the idea of sending a message to Maximoff through a radio. She also gave Foster advice during her chemotherapy.
{{Quote|I just need to hack into the secure network on the base. Donezo. Now, should be able to access the data on [[Tyler Hayward|Hayward]]'s devices.|Darcy Lewis to [[Monica Rambeau]] and [[Jimmy Woo]]|All-New Halloween Spooktacular!}}
*'''Expert Hacker''': Lewis possesses expert hacking skills, and was skillful enough to hack [[S.W.O.R.D.]]'s database and access Acting Director [[Tyler Hayward]]'s personal files. In the file she found Hayward's plans to use [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] as a weapon.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''Taser''': Lewis had wielded a taser, which she initially used to stun [[Thor]], when she believed him belligerent, upon his arrival from the [[Bifrost Bridge]]. Once Lewis heard that Thor had escaped from hospital, she rearmed the taser, ready to use it against him again.

===Other Equipment===
*'''[[Phase Meter]]''': Lewis saw [[Erik Selvig]]'s phase meter acting up and used it along with [[Ian Boothby]] and [[Jane Foster]] to find a warehouse which was being affected by the coming [[Convergence]].
*'''[[Gravimetric Spike]]''': Lewis and [[Ian Boothby]] went to various spots in Greenwich and set up gravimetric spikes to defeat [[Malekith]].
*'''CMBR Meter:''' Lewis brought equipment to the [[S.W.O.R.D. Response Base]] outside Westview, New Jersey and detected a colossal amount of Cosmic Microwave Background Radiation.
*'''Spectrum Analyzer:''' Lewis detected longer wavelengths over the CMBR with her spectrum analyzer and engineered a solution to provide the first visuals into the [[Westview Anomaly]] using an old Physio-Scope and a CRT television set.

===Vehicles===
*'''Pinzgauer 710K high-mobility all-terrain 4WD (4×4)''': [[Jane Foster]] dragged Lewis and [[Erik Selvig]] to the desert in a campervan. Suddenly, [[Thor]] dropped out of the sky, where they crashed into him.
*'''Volvo 240 Series wagon:''' Lewis drives [[Mighty Thor|Jane Foster]] and [[Ian Boothby]] to the warehouse in London where the equipment is registering the anomalous physics leading up to the [[Convergence]].
*'''1950 Grumman-Olson Kurb Side walk-in van:''' After being absorbed into the expanded [[Westview Anomaly]] (the Hex) and released from [[Scarlet Witch|Wanda Maximoff]]'s mind control by [[Vision]], Lewis drives Vision back into Westview, New Jersey in a "Funnel of Love" food truck stolen from the circus of former [[S.W.O.R.D.]] agents.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Culver University]]''': Lewis studied political science at Culver University and became [[Erik Selvig]]'s intern.
*'''[[Smith Motors]]''': Lewis, [[Erik Selvig]], and [[Jane Foster]] used Smith Motors as their research base, until their data was taken by [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]. The group then stayed at Smith Motors and discussed the organization's actions.
*'''[[Jane Foster's Apartment]]:''' Lewis and [[Mighty Thor|Jane Foster]] used Foster's late mother's apartment in London as a lab when they traveled there to collaborate with [[Erik Selvig]] on the [[Convergence]].
*'''Tromsø, Norway Observatory:''' [[Phil Coulson]] arranged a fake job opportunity for [[Mighty Thor|Jane Foster]] to work with [[Hilgard|Dr. Hilgard]] at an observatory in Tromsø, Norway. Lewis accompanied Jane as her assistant and circumvented [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] firewalls and security protocols and discovered that Thor was in New York fighting the [[Chitauri Invasion]].
*'''[[S.W.O.R.D. Response Base]]''': Lewis was brought to [[S.W.O.R.D.]]'s response base to study the [[Westview Anomaly]] and advocated for [[Wanda Maximoff]] alongside [[Monica Rambeau]] and [[Jimmy Woo]], while investigating what Maximoff had done to [[Westview]]. She chose to stay after Woo and Rambeau escaped the facility, discovering that [[Tyler Hayward]] was secretly operating [[Project Cataract]]. She saw that [[Vision/Chaos Magic Recreation|Vision]] was attempting to escape Westview, so she rushed to help him, only to get arrested by [[Monti]]. This led to Lewis getting brought under Maximoff's spell when she expanded the borders of it.

