==Trivia==
*Darcy Lewis was created specifically for the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]. In 2023, her character was added into the mainstream [[Marvel Comics (publisher)|Marvel Comics]] continuity, debuting in ''[[w:c:marvel:Scarlet Witch Vol 3|Scarlet Witch Vol 3]]''. This version of Darcy Lewis was a journalist in desperate need of a good story who infiltrated the [[w:c:marvel:Bacchae (Earth-616)|Bacchae]], a secret cult of warrior women. When it was revealed that she was researching the group, Darcy panicked and killed one of the Baccae's sisters in self-defense. She then went on the run, eventually being brought to the [[Scarlet Witch]]'s [[w:c:marvel:Emporium|Emporium]] by the [[w:c:marvel:Last Door|Last Door]], where she started working.

==Behind the Scenes==
*According to [[Zack Stentz]], the co-screenwriter of ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'', the Lewis character was originally conceived as a middle-aged man with a son when he was working on the script. The character was then rewritten by co-screenwriter [[Don Payne]] to be a young woman.<ref>[https://twitter.com/MuseZack/status/1367331811659972609 Zack Stentz on Twitter - March 4, 2021]</ref>
*Early drafts for ''[[WandaVision]]'' had flashbacks revealing that Lewis pawned her grandmother's old television after she was a victim of the [[Snap]]. However, after her grandmother returned in the [[Blip]], Lewis reacquired the television and became aware of the [[Hex]] when she plugged the TV in. The idea was then discarded for feeling too much a detour.<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/tv-features/oral-history-wandavision-olsen-bettany-hahn-feige-1155120/ The Oral History of ‘WandaVision’]</ref>
*[[Christine Renaud]] was a double for [[Kat Dennings]] in ''[[On a Very Special Episode...]]'' and ''[[All-New Halloween Spooktacular!]]''.
*[[Cat Hannah]], [[Dani Biernat]], [[Athena Perample]] and [[Heather Bonomo]] were stunt doubles for Kat Dennings in the role of Darcy Lewis.
*[[Hannah Louise Pritchard]] was a stand-in and a double for Kat Dennings in the role of Darcy Lewis.

